French Embroidery Beading is used to decorate and embellish clothing, mainly women's fashion frocks and gowns. As fashions change, so do beading designs.

This books covers all the basic techniques and provides numerous designs which can easily be made on sweaters, blouses, headbands, handbags, collars, bras and even lampshades.

The book is lavishly illustrated in colour with examples of the author's work. Maisie Jarratt has been embroidering with beads for over fifty years and has spent much of this time teaching others the art
